C29b11a.xml:<note>Carter wrote to his son-in-law, Mann Page, <xref doc="C29b11b">this same day</xref> noting that he sends his letter to the governor by Charles, and has left it open so that Page can decide whether to send it or not. The minutes of a meeting of the Council held 1729 November 1 show that Charles did replace his brother as naval officer of the Rappahannock. (<cit><bibl n="B10">McIlwaine. <title>Executive Journals of the Council. . . .</title>, 4[1721-1739]:210. </bibl></cit> )</note>
