C29c04a.xml:<note id="n2">[2] Carter refers to a letter he had written to Lee <xref doc="C29b24a">1729 February 24</xref>.</note>
C31f23a.xml:<note id="n7">[7] Landon Carter (1710-1778) was Carter's seventh child by his second wife, Elizabeth (Landon) Willis. Landon would live at "Sabine Hall," Richmond County, and marry three times, leaving many descendants, some of whom own "Sabine Hall" today. As an adult, he would keep a very interesting and useful diary. A reproduction of a portrait of him may be found on the website of the <xref doc="http://www.christchurch1735.org/history/robert_carter.html">Foundation of Historic Christ Church.</xref> (<cit><bibl n="B30">Greene. <title>The Diary of Colonel Landon Carter. . . .</title></bibl></cit>)</note>
